WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:03.002
- [smooches]
URSULA: Ahhh...

00:04.254 --> 00:05.922
- Girls, Ursula and I

00:06.005 --> 00:07.590
have something to tell you.

00:07.674 --> 00:09.926
Something amazing!

00:10.009 --> 00:11.928
- Ooh, you're moving back
to New Transylvania?

00:12.011 --> 00:14.639
Or wherever it is
you're from.

00:14.723 --> 00:16.516
- No.
[laughs]

00:16.599 --> 00:18.435
We...

00:18.518 --> 00:19.769
We're in love!

00:19.853 --> 00:20.478
EMMA &amp; MADDIE:
No, you're not!

00:20.562 --> 00:23.440
- We are?

00:23.523 --> 00:24.941
We are!

00:25.024 --> 00:27.694
- And we wanna get married
as soon as possible.

00:27.777 --> 00:29.779
- Wahooooo!

00:29.863 --> 00:31.239
[laughing]

00:31.322 --> 00:34.117
Oh, isn't this wonderful,
girls?

00:34.200 --> 00:37.078
You're gonna be sisters,
eh?

00:38.747 --> 00:41.875
- No-o-o-o-o-o!

00:41.958 --> 00:44.210
- No, Dad! Really, no!

00:45.545 --> 00:46.504
- Why is Maddie crying?

00:46.588 --> 00:48.965
- She's crying tears of joy.

00:49.048 --> 00:50.675
Tears of joy!

00:54.763 --> 00:56.306
- What is going on?

00:56.389 --> 00:58.308
- I don't know!
Why are you asking me?

00:58.391 --> 01:00.101
- Because this is
obviously your fault!

01:00.185 --> 01:00.894
- Obvious how?

01:00.977 --> 01:02.812
- Obvious in the fact that

01:02.896 --> 01:04.480
it clearly isn't my fault!

01:04.563 --> 01:05.648
- Your mom's the one
who's been after my dad

01:05.732 --> 01:08.151
for the past year!

01:08.234 --> 01:09.986
- Yeah, but your dad's
the one who's dumb enough

01:10.069 --> 01:11.362
to fall for my mom!

01:12.405 --> 01:15.241
- I have to give you that one.
But...

01:15.325 --> 01:16.326
But this makes no sense.

01:16.409 --> 01:19.120
Yesterday, he was mowing
the lawn at night

01:19.204 --> 01:22.123
so your mom wouldn't
"accidentally" run into him.

01:22.207 --> 01:23.500
- It's like somebody cast
a spell on him or something.

01:23.583 --> 01:26.002
[gasps] Wait!

01:26.085 --> 01:27.629
Did you get your powers back
and not tell me?

01:27.712 --> 01:29.380
- No...

01:29.464 --> 01:31.174
But Andi said you did.

01:31.257 --> 01:33.343
- Sort of. It's complicated.
[laughs]

01:33.426 --> 01:35.595
But I didn't do this.

01:35.678 --> 01:36.805
- Okay, I believe you.

01:36.888 --> 01:39.516
We just need to figure out
how this happened

01:39.599 --> 01:40.809
so we can stop it.

01:40.892 --> 01:42.685
Neither of us
want to be sisters.

01:42.769 --> 01:44.103
We need to work together.
Agreed?

01:47.315 --> 01:48.233
- Agreed!

01:50.777 --> 01:52.737
{\an8}<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

01:52.821 --> 01:55.573
{\an8}<i>WOMAN: ♪ I cast a spell ♪</i>

01:55.657 --> 01:57.408
{\an8}<i>♪ It takes a hold of you ♪</i>

01:57.492 --> 01:59.118
{\an8}<i>♪ I see my dreams ♪</i>

01:59.202 --> 02:00.954
{\an8}<i>♪ And they're all</i>
<i>coming true ♪</i>

02:01.037 --> 02:01.913
{\an8}<i>♪ Come on ♪</i>

02:01.996 --> 02:02.914
{\an8}<i>♪ Let's go ♪</i>

02:02.997 --> 02:04.707
{\an8}<i>♪ You and me together ♪</i>

02:04.791 --> 02:05.917
{\an8}<i>♪ Look up ahead ♪</i>

02:06.000 --> 02:08.377
{\an8}<i>♪ There's a magical adventure ♪</i>

02:08.461 --> 02:09.753
{\an8}<i>♪ Every witch way ♪</i>

02:09.838 --> 02:11.506
{\an8}<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

02:11.589 --> 02:12.715
<i>♪ I'm trying</i>
<i>every witch way ♪</i>

02:12.799 --> 02:14.342
<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

02:14.425 --> 02:17.428
<i>♪ I'm going</i>
<i>every witch way ♪</i>

02:17.512 --> 02:19.430
<i>♪ Ay-ay-ay-ay-ay ♪</i>

02:19.514 --> 02:20.723
<i>♪ Every witch way ♪</i>

02:22.934 --> 02:23.810
{\an8}- [scoffs]
This smoothie is warm.

02:23.893 --> 02:24.853
{\an8}Proxy!
- Here!

02:24.936 --> 02:26.938
{\an8}- Freeze it for me.

02:28.231 --> 02:29.190
{\an8}[snaps fingers] Locker!

02:31.526 --> 02:32.569
[snaps fingers] Books!

02:36.990 --> 02:38.908
[snaps fingers] Lip gloss!

02:38.992 --> 02:39.993
[laughs]

02:45.164 --> 02:47.584
- Oh, here--
one frozen smoothie.

02:47.667 --> 02:49.252
- Be faster next time.

02:49.335 --> 02:51.838
Same for you.
What's taking so long?

02:51.921 --> 02:53.506
- I'm not sure
what class you have next.

02:53.590 --> 02:56.259
- Really?
- She has History.

02:56.342 --> 02:58.720
- Oh, no, I didn't do
Maddie's History essay.

02:58.803 --> 02:59.929
That's due today.

03:00.013 --> 03:01.306
- You didn't what?

03:02.557 --> 03:04.601
Proxy, rain on Sophie!

03:04.684 --> 03:05.768
- No need for that.

03:05.852 --> 03:07.270
I wrote two History essays.

03:07.353 --> 03:09.314
One on the roles
that women played

03:09.397 --> 03:10.315
in the
Progressive Era reforms

03:10.398 --> 03:13.276
from the 1800s
through the 1920s.

03:13.359 --> 03:15.945
And then, for fun,
I compared and contrast

03:16.029 --> 03:17.614
the foreign policies
of Teddy Roosevelt

03:17.697 --> 03:18.781
and Woodrow Wilson.

03:18.865 --> 03:19.908
- Ooh, don't keep me
in suspense.

03:19.991 --> 03:21.451
Whose policies were better?

03:21.534 --> 03:23.202
- They have more in common
than you would think--

03:23.286 --> 03:26.122
- Just give it to me.
Stop!

03:26.205 --> 03:27.665
Proxy, rain on Katie.

03:28.541 --> 03:31.544
- Wait!
Think of the essays.

03:31.628 --> 03:32.837
- You're right.

03:32.921 --> 03:34.339
Proxy, stop.

03:34.422 --> 03:37.133
- So...
which one do you want?

03:37.216 --> 03:39.677
- I don't care.

03:39.761 --> 03:41.638
I guess...

03:41.721 --> 03:43.139
the one about
the teddy bears.

03:43.222 --> 03:44.265
- Teddy Roosevelt it is.

03:50.271 --> 03:52.190
- Let me get this straight.

03:52.273 --> 03:55.360
Your father and Mrs. Van Pelt--

03:55.443 --> 03:57.153
getting married?

03:57.236 --> 03:58.821
- It was so weird.

03:58.905 --> 04:00.573
One minute, he's like,
"I'm gonna have to

04:00.657 --> 04:03.993
get another restraining order
on Mrs. Van Pelt."

04:04.077 --> 04:06.788
And the next,
he's all '80s love songs

04:06.871 --> 04:10.416
and, "Would you like
more ice cream, Ursy-Wursy?"

04:11.626 --> 04:13.962
I mean, I don't know her
very well.

04:14.045 --> 04:16.589
Maybe she's nice?

04:16.673 --> 04:19.007
- I mean...she can be,

04:19.091 --> 04:20.259
in that crazy,

04:20.343 --> 04:22.512
"don't give her any more
caffeine" kind of way.

04:24.055 --> 04:25.264
- I need to sneak
right on by.

04:27.183 --> 04:29.978
Make me a spider
so I can be a good spy.

04:30.061 --> 04:32.021
[powers zapping]

04:32.105 --> 04:36.192
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:36.275 --> 04:37.026
- I just thought he disliked
Mrs. Van Pelt

04:37.110 --> 04:39.320
more than he dislikes me.

04:39.404 --> 04:40.655
EMMA: He doesn't.

04:40.738 --> 04:43.533
You're way at the top
of his dislike list.

04:43.616 --> 04:45.076
- I tried to win him over.

04:45.159 --> 04:47.203
It's just, most of my plans...
backfired.

04:47.286 --> 04:49.998
- Yep, and backfired
chocolate pudding

04:50.081 --> 04:50.790
all over his favorite shirt.

04:50.873 --> 04:53.376
- The T3 did that.

04:53.459 --> 04:54.836
I just took the rap.

04:54.919 --> 04:56.838
- Well, lucky for you,
he's barely mentioned that

04:56.921 --> 04:59.799
ever since he fell in love
with his...Ursy-Wursy.

04:59.882 --> 05:04.512
- Maybe they got to talking
and started liking each other.

05:04.595 --> 05:06.639
- No, that's just it.

05:06.723 --> 05:08.641
It was like something
suddenly changed.

05:09.642 --> 05:12.061
Almost like a spell
or something.

05:12.145 --> 05:13.896
- Well, that can't be.

05:13.980 --> 05:15.148
- Why not?

05:15.231 --> 05:18.067
- Because you lost your powers
and so did Maddie.

05:18.151 --> 05:20.236
So there's no one else left
to cast a spell.

05:20.319 --> 05:21.904
- Yeah, uh, right!

05:21.988 --> 05:24.198
Listen, Daniel...

05:25.658 --> 05:26.409
- I mean, I can come over
after school

05:26.492 --> 05:27.452
and help you look for clues.

05:30.163 --> 05:31.414
- Giant spider!

05:31.497 --> 05:33.249
[students screaming]

05:33.332 --> 05:35.501
- Run, everybody, run!
- Where?

05:35.585 --> 05:36.627
- There, by the door!

05:38.129 --> 05:39.005
- Got it!

05:39.088 --> 05:40.048
- He got it!
Sebastian got it!

05:40.131 --> 05:42.592
We can relax now.

05:42.675 --> 05:45.261
Oh, no, I'm injured.

05:45.344 --> 05:52.393
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:11.871 --> 06:12.622
- [laughs]

06:12.705 --> 06:14.707
Hmm...

06:16.084 --> 06:17.960
Ooh, what's this?

06:21.297 --> 06:22.381
- Andi, why are you here?

06:22.465 --> 06:25.426
And why are you dressed
like the nurse?

06:25.510 --> 06:27.095
- Because I am the nurse.

06:27.178 --> 06:29.013
- What?
No, you're not.

06:29.097 --> 06:31.140
I know for a fact
that Nurse Lily moved away

06:31.224 --> 06:33.684
and Principal Alonso
hasn't found a replacement yet.

06:33.768 --> 06:35.561
- Which is why he hired me.

06:35.645 --> 06:36.854
Since my dad's a...
[clears throat]

06:36.938 --> 06:41.150
Doctor, I'm qualified to be
the interim nurse.

06:41.234 --> 06:44.654
- So the Principal hired
his daughter's best friend.

06:44.737 --> 06:46.864
That is an abuse of power!

06:46.948 --> 06:48.825
You can read about it
on Miss Information.

06:48.908 --> 06:50.159
- What? Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!

06:50.243 --> 06:51.869
- So Shark tryouts
are at 3:00.

06:51.953 --> 06:54.539
Kickboards, flipboards,
and arm floaties aren't allowed.

06:54.622 --> 06:58.000
- I'd assume
that's a given, right?

06:58.084 --> 06:59.669
- You'd be surprised.

06:59.752 --> 07:01.838
<i>[bugle music]</i>

07:01.921 --> 07:04.048
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:04.132 --> 07:07.176
- Thank you. Thank you.

07:08.594 --> 07:11.180
- That's weird.
- Tell me about it.

07:11.264 --> 07:12.515
That's my girlfriend's dad.

07:15.476 --> 07:17.603
- You ready? There's two
empty seats over there.

07:19.647 --> 07:21.190
[powers zapping]
[drink explodes]

07:21.274 --> 07:23.359
URSULA: [screams]
Daniel!

07:24.569 --> 07:25.945
- Daniel,
look what you've done!

07:26.028 --> 07:29.073
Not just to me
but to my beloved Ursy-Wursy.

07:29.157 --> 07:30.741
- Uh...I...
Uh...I...

07:30.825 --> 07:32.577
- Oh, it's all right,
Franciscy-Winkie.

07:32.660 --> 07:35.913
You don't have to worry
about little old me.

07:35.997 --> 07:38.249
- Don't you have anything
to say for yourself?

07:38.332 --> 07:40.293
- At least it was chocolate milk
this time and not pudding.

07:40.376 --> 07:43.462
- [laughs] Detention! Today!
After school!

07:43.546 --> 07:45.298
- But I'm supposed to help Emma
with her...

07:45.381 --> 07:48.134
Homework.
- Yeah, right.

07:48.217 --> 07:50.261
I've seen your grades, okay?

07:50.344 --> 07:52.638
She doesn't need your help.

07:52.722 --> 07:54.265
You know what?
No, come with me.

07:54.348 --> 07:55.683
Come with me.
Come on. Come on.

07:55.766 --> 07:57.226
Honey, come on.
I'm so sorry.

07:57.310 --> 08:01.480
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:01.564 --> 08:03.733
- I think it's kind of cool
that Mr. Alonso and your mom--

08:03.816 --> 08:06.152
- Can you freeze
your mouth shut, pronto?

08:06.235 --> 08:07.737
- I'm just saying that
Mr. Alonso's a very cool--

08:07.820 --> 08:09.197
- I get it!

08:09.280 --> 08:12.241
You like Mr. Alonso,
video games, and cooking.

08:12.325 --> 08:13.576
Your favorite food
is spaghetti.

08:13.659 --> 08:16.037
You miss Mac, and your
fastest time in the 100-meter

08:16.120 --> 08:18.748
individual medley is two minutes
and ten seconds.

08:18.831 --> 08:19.874
Your favorite condiment is...
- [laughing]

08:19.957 --> 08:22.710
You were listening.
- Is cayenne pepper.

08:26.047 --> 08:28.257
Who has a favorite condiment?
You're so weird.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.426
- Everybody.
- I want that girl's compact.

08:30.509 --> 08:32.803
Get it for me, proxy.
- What's a compact?

08:32.886 --> 08:34.096
- That little round
shiny thing right there.

08:34.179 --> 08:35.640
- But it's not yours.
It's Ashley's.

08:35.722 --> 08:38.851
- Ashley and I share things
all the time.

08:38.934 --> 08:40.436
She won't mind.
Now get it!

08:44.440 --> 08:45.650
- [sighs]

08:51.864 --> 08:52.657
- Great!
[laughs]

08:58.246 --> 08:58.663
- Hmm...

09:03.543 --> 09:05.544
Spell-O-Vision?

09:05.628 --> 09:08.172
Cool! I always wanted these.
[laughs]

09:15.888 --> 09:17.723
- Take five, proxy.

09:19.141 --> 09:20.768
This better be good.

09:20.851 --> 09:24.188
- My dad wants to buy your mom
an engagement ring.

09:24.272 --> 09:26.565
Is that good enough?
- Don't panic.

09:26.649 --> 09:28.609
He can't afford anything
my mom would like.

09:28.693 --> 09:30.486
- Good point.

09:30.569 --> 09:33.030
Hey, don't start
picking on my dad!

09:33.114 --> 09:34.991
It's your mom who's after him.
- You wish!

09:35.074 --> 09:37.618
- How do I know you didn't
cast a spell on him?

09:37.702 --> 09:38.744
- Because I can't.
I don't have my powers ba--

09:38.828 --> 09:41.998
- But Andi saw you
cast a spell on a pen.

09:42.081 --> 09:44.583
- Oh, that, yeah.
That was proxy.

09:44.667 --> 09:48.337
- What's proxy?
- Not what, who.

09:48.421 --> 09:51.591
You know, that guy with
the strange weather powers.

09:51.674 --> 09:53.843
- Diego?
- Yeah, that guy.

09:53.926 --> 09:57.555
I want magical things to happen,
he does them for me.

09:57.638 --> 09:59.557
- And Diego's okay with you
using him?

09:59.640 --> 10:01.684
- [laughs] He's delighted.

10:01.767 --> 10:03.144
Are you done with
my private life?

10:03.227 --> 10:04.687
- Yes. What do you think
we should do?

10:04.770 --> 10:07.481
- I think we should
make their lives miserable

10:07.565 --> 10:09.442
till they decide
to stop this nonsense.

10:09.525 --> 10:10.901
[laughs]

10:14.447 --> 10:16.699
- What are you doing?

10:16.782 --> 10:17.700
- My locker got moved,
so I'm taking yours.

10:17.783 --> 10:20.661
- No, you're not.
- Yes, I am.

10:20.745 --> 10:23.664
As the future Principal's
stepdaughter,

10:23.748 --> 10:25.708
I can take any locker I want.
- No, you can't!

10:25.791 --> 10:29.003
As the actual daughter
of the Principal,

10:29.086 --> 10:30.504
I say you can't.

10:30.588 --> 10:33.257
- See, everybody,
this is favoritism.

10:33.341 --> 10:34.633
Plain and simple.
- No, it's not.

10:34.717 --> 10:36.510
- What's going on here?
- Emma started it.

10:36.594 --> 10:39.430
- Maddie wants to steal
my locker.

10:39.513 --> 10:42.350
- Oh, they're already
fighting like sisters.

10:42.433 --> 10:44.352
- She thinks because
she's the Principal's

10:44.435 --> 10:47.104
future stepdaughter,
she can do whatever she wants.

10:47.188 --> 10:49.398
- Please, I already do
whatever I want.

10:49.482 --> 10:50.649
It's Emma who's acting
all crazy now.

10:50.733 --> 10:53.694
- Look, if you both
want the same locker,

10:53.778 --> 10:55.071
why don't you just share it?

10:55.154 --> 10:57.239
- Sharing?
- You're taking her side?

10:57.323 --> 10:59.658
- I'm taking the side
of no fights.

10:59.742 --> 11:00.451
- I see what's going on here.

11:00.534 --> 11:03.079
- You do?
- Mm-hmm.

11:03.162 --> 11:05.915
Now that you two
are gonna be sisters,

11:05.998 --> 11:07.416
you wanna be
next to each other.

11:07.500 --> 11:10.836
Isn't that sweet? Oh...

11:10.920 --> 11:12.171
- That is great.

11:12.254 --> 11:13.714
You know, I'll tell you what.

11:13.798 --> 11:16.175
I'll find two empty lockers
next to each other

11:16.258 --> 11:17.593
and I'll assign it
to both of you.

11:17.676 --> 11:19.762
- Oh, that's perfect!
- Ha!

11:19.845 --> 11:20.805
- Perfect!

11:23.432 --> 11:26.143
- That didn't go as planned.
- Yeah.

11:26.227 --> 11:28.354
I mean, I'm all
for working together on this.

11:28.437 --> 11:30.398
But I don't wanna be
locker neighbors.

11:35.736 --> 11:37.905
- I made it! I made it, yeah!

11:37.988 --> 11:40.866
- This is detention,
Mr. Miller, not a party.

11:40.950 --> 11:42.868
But I'm glad
you're happy to be here.

11:49.500 --> 11:51.168
- Hey, Gigi,
why are you here?

11:51.252 --> 11:53.546
- For breaking
important news.

11:53.629 --> 11:57.133
This school has
no freedom of speech.

11:58.592 --> 12:01.804
I didn't have a picture of
Mr. Alonso and Mrs. Van Pelt

12:01.887 --> 12:03.931
for my "Franciscula"

12:04.014 --> 12:06.308
Principal-Parent Romance
article.

12:08.227 --> 12:09.437
So I published this.

12:09.520 --> 12:10.729
- [laughs] What?

12:12.398 --> 12:14.567
- What's so funny, Mr. Miller?
- Uh...

12:17.194 --> 12:18.821
[doorbell rings]

12:21.991 --> 12:24.410
- Hey, uh--Jax?

12:25.536 --> 12:26.996
- Hey, Emma.

12:27.079 --> 12:28.456
Heard you were
having some trouble

12:28.539 --> 12:31.500
with your dad
and Maddie's mom.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.919
I'd be happy to help.

12:34.003 --> 12:35.463
- Who told you that?

12:35.546 --> 12:37.214
- [laughs] No one.
I'm a wizard.

12:37.298 --> 12:39.133
- A wizard, not a psychic.

12:39.216 --> 12:41.886
- Yeah, well, in my case,
same thing.

12:41.969 --> 12:43.345
Watch.

12:43.429 --> 12:47.016
I predict that you'll trip
on your way to the kitchen.

12:47.099 --> 12:49.977
- Nice try. I'm not going
into the kitchen.

12:50.060 --> 12:52.980
[powers zapping]

12:53.063 --> 12:55.065
[soap bubbles gurgling]

12:55.149 --> 12:56.650
Hey!

12:56.734 --> 12:59.195
[powers zapping]

12:59.278 --> 13:00.279
- Gotcha.

13:01.530 --> 13:02.573
- Thanks.

13:06.619 --> 13:08.579
Wait, you're the one
that made me trip

13:08.662 --> 13:10.206
in the first place.

13:10.289 --> 13:11.874
I take that thanks back.

13:11.957 --> 13:14.043
- But I still predicted
the future, didn't I?

13:14.126 --> 13:16.086
- [sighs]
- Oh, come on.

13:16.170 --> 13:17.880
I just wanna help.

13:17.963 --> 13:19.381
- It's okay.

13:19.465 --> 13:20.424
I'm actually waiting
for someone else.

13:20.508 --> 13:23.219
- Who? Daniel?

13:23.302 --> 13:25.721
It'll be a while before
he gets back from detention.

13:25.804 --> 13:28.432
- I promised I'd wait
for him.

13:28.516 --> 13:32.061
- And by that time,
your dad'll probably be home.

13:32.144 --> 13:34.188
Word on the street
is that your dad

13:34.271 --> 13:35.397
doesn't like Daniel at all.

13:35.481 --> 13:37.274
- Well...

13:37.358 --> 13:39.151
- Well, it's settled then.

13:39.235 --> 13:41.111
Put me to work.

13:41.195 --> 13:42.238
What can I do for you?

13:46.492 --> 13:48.452
I don't understand
what you're doing.

13:48.536 --> 13:50.246
- Your house must be
really dirty

13:50.329 --> 13:51.914
if you've never seen
anyone do this.

13:51.997 --> 13:53.916
- I mean, just cast a spell.

13:53.999 --> 13:55.084
- I don't want to.

13:55.167 --> 13:58.087
- Why not?
- So I can appreciate the work.

13:58.170 --> 14:00.631
Have a sense
of accomplishment.

14:00.714 --> 14:02.258
I did this.

14:02.341 --> 14:03.592
- You get a sense of
accomplishment from mopping?

14:03.676 --> 14:06.470
- Yes.
Maybe you would, too,

14:06.554 --> 14:08.597
if you ever tried.

14:08.681 --> 14:08.931
- Doubt it.

14:11.350 --> 14:14.645
- I'm gonna go change.
- Why don't you just--

14:14.728 --> 14:16.897
- I'm going to go change.
- [laughs] Okay.

14:27.116 --> 14:28.742
[powers zapping]

14:36.417 --> 14:37.876
[powers zapping]

14:43.966 --> 14:45.426
- What?

14:45.509 --> 14:46.635
Did I do that?

14:46.719 --> 14:49.471
No.
- What are you drawing?

14:49.555 --> 14:50.931
[laughing]

14:57.730 --> 14:59.023
- Is this supposed to be me?
- No, uh...

14:59.106 --> 15:01.525
- Then why does it say
"Mr. Alonso" on the bottom?

15:01.609 --> 15:03.861
- I don't know.
I swear.

15:03.944 --> 15:06.071
- Um, maybe you meant
Mr. Alonso

15:06.155 --> 15:07.906
the mailman
in our neighborhood.

15:07.990 --> 15:09.408
<i>Right, Daniel?</i>

15:10.492 --> 15:12.661
- Our mailman's name
is Mr. Alonso?

15:14.246 --> 15:15.331
- You're a lost cause.

15:15.414 --> 15:16.498
- [laughing]

15:16.582 --> 15:18.292
<i>MR. ALONSO:</i>
<i>You think this is funny,</i>

15:18.375 --> 15:19.376
hmm?

15:20.753 --> 15:23.672
Let's see how a week
in detention suits you.

15:24.923 --> 15:26.383
Gigi. Phone. Down!

15:29.094 --> 15:30.971
- [laughing]

15:31.055 --> 15:32.264
Best movie yet.

15:33.349 --> 15:36.226
- Come on, Mr. Miller,
to the board.

15:36.310 --> 15:38.270
I want you to write 100 times:

15:38.354 --> 15:40.898
"I will not make fun
of Mr. Alonso."

15:50.949 --> 15:53.160
- New plot twist.

15:53.243 --> 15:56.830
"I will play tricks
on Mr. Alonso

15:56.914 --> 15:59.041
all year."
[laughing]

15:59.124 --> 16:00.125
<i>- No.</i>
<i>This can't be happening again.</i>

16:14.723 --> 16:16.308
[powers zapping]
- All changed.

16:16.392 --> 16:18.102
- Great.

16:18.185 --> 16:19.353
Ready to help.

16:19.436 --> 16:22.022
- That's okay.
I'll wait for Daniel.

16:22.106 --> 16:26.110
- [sighs] Daniel's not
one of us, Emma.

16:27.986 --> 16:30.072
You can't be asking him
for help.

16:30.155 --> 16:31.615
- You can trust him.

16:31.699 --> 16:33.242
I trust him completely.

16:33.325 --> 16:34.743
- Then why didn't you
tell him about

16:34.827 --> 16:36.495
having your powers back?

16:36.578 --> 16:39.415
- It's...
It's complicated.

16:39.498 --> 16:41.125
- Well, explain it to me.

16:43.001 --> 16:44.253
Oh, come on.

16:44.336 --> 16:46.755
How many other teenaged witches
or wizards do you know

16:46.839 --> 16:48.424
that you can talk to
about this?

16:48.507 --> 16:56.223
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:56.306 --> 17:00.894
So Maddie lost her powers,
but you got yours back?

17:00.978 --> 17:03.772
- Pretty much.
Want some pie?

17:03.856 --> 17:05.773
Mrs. Van Pelt brought it over
for my dad.

17:05.858 --> 17:07.608
Homemade, straight
from the store.

17:07.693 --> 17:09.778
- Um, I'm good, thanks.

17:10.820 --> 17:12.030
[doorbell rings]

17:15.032 --> 17:16.952
ALL: ♪ Hello ♪

17:17.035 --> 17:19.288
- Terribles?
What are you doing here?

17:19.371 --> 17:22.124
- Daniel couldn't make it,
so he sent us to help.

17:22.207 --> 17:24.126
- They know too?
- No.

17:24.209 --> 17:27.378
They're just really good
at finding things.

17:27.463 --> 17:30.549
- Know what?
- [laughs]

17:30.632 --> 17:31.675
Isn't that cute?

17:31.759 --> 17:34.636
Daniel sent his little siblings
to replace him.

17:36.096 --> 17:39.057
- Who are you?
- What are you doing here?

17:39.141 --> 17:40.809
- And who are you calling
little and cute?

17:40.893 --> 17:43.771
- Jax was just leaving.
- I was?

17:50.986 --> 17:53.238
- So how are you going
to help?

17:53.322 --> 17:55.532
- We're going to lift prints
inside your house

17:55.616 --> 17:58.577
and see if anybody's been there
that shouldn't have been.

17:58.660 --> 18:00.412
- You have that kind
of technology?

18:00.496 --> 18:01.997
- Yeah. Duh!

18:02.080 --> 18:04.500
- But, first,
we need some baby powder.

18:04.583 --> 18:06.210
- Come on, I think
I have some in my room.

18:13.425 --> 18:16.011
- Oooh, pie.
- Wait.

18:16.095 --> 18:18.096
Make sure it isn't
booby-trapped.

18:20.599 --> 18:22.017
- It's clean.

18:26.230 --> 18:28.941
- Oh, hey, T3,
what are you doing?

18:29.024 --> 18:31.276
- [muffled]
We're having some pi--

18:31.360 --> 18:33.028
- Why are you looking at me
like that?

18:35.489 --> 18:40.035
- So, yeah, "Operation Break Up"
is not going well.

18:40.118 --> 18:42.538
I don't know what is wrong
with my dad.

18:42.621 --> 18:46.208
- He also gave me detention
for the rest of the month--

18:46.291 --> 18:47.751
except for today.

18:47.835 --> 18:50.379
We have tryouts to find
a new Shark.

18:50.462 --> 18:53.048
He must be really mad at me.
- He is.

18:53.131 --> 18:54.341
But, lucky for you,

18:54.424 --> 18:56.718
Mrs. Van Pelt
is distracting him.

18:56.802 --> 18:57.845
Though I rather he obsess
over your punishment

18:57.928 --> 19:00.138
than marry Mrs. Van Pelt.

19:01.682 --> 19:02.850
Come on, if you were me,

19:02.933 --> 19:03.559
wouldn't you feel
the same way?

19:03.642 --> 19:05.894
- Okay, I might.

19:05.978 --> 19:08.605
- Oh, thanks for sending
the T3 over to help yesterday.

19:08.689 --> 19:11.275
- Did they, um, find anything?
- Not really.

19:11.358 --> 19:13.068
Tommy and Rob just stuffed
themselves with pie

19:13.151 --> 19:15.237
and Mel covered the house
in baby powder.

19:15.320 --> 19:17.239
- [laughs] That sounds
about right.

19:17.322 --> 19:19.992
Um...when they were
at your house,

19:20.075 --> 19:22.578
did Andi give them some
cool new tools or something?

19:22.661 --> 19:23.912
- I don't think so. Why?

19:23.996 --> 19:25.789
- Tommy and Rob came home,
and they could not stop

19:25.873 --> 19:27.207
talking about Andi
and how she's

19:27.291 --> 19:28.750
the coolest girl
in the world.

19:28.834 --> 19:30.294
- Oh, that's sweet.

19:33.547 --> 19:36.133
- I need you to get me
Sebastian's homework

19:36.216 --> 19:37.509
from his backpack.

19:37.593 --> 19:38.302
Sophie forgot mine--
again.

19:40.804 --> 19:42.472
- No.
- What's that?

19:42.556 --> 19:43.932
- I'm not stealing
his homework.

19:44.016 --> 19:46.351
You should have done yours.

19:46.435 --> 19:48.270
- Proxy, how dare you!

19:48.353 --> 19:51.356
- My name isn't proxy,
it's Diego.

19:51.440 --> 19:52.733
And I'm totally over this.

19:52.816 --> 19:54.276
I'm not stealing stuff
for you anymore.

19:54.359 --> 19:56.737
- It's not stealing,
it's borrowing!

20:09.875 --> 20:11.627
- Okay, we have
some good times here.

20:11.710 --> 20:13.211
But, as a reminder,
no cannonballs.

20:17.716 --> 20:19.259
- All right, I...

20:19.343 --> 20:22.054
Only Jax left,
and I guess he'll race...

20:22.137 --> 20:23.138
you.

20:24.723 --> 20:25.891
- Okay, let's do this.

20:28.727 --> 20:30.103
- I have to warn you--

20:30.187 --> 20:32.481
Daniel broke the national
freestyle record last year.

20:32.564 --> 20:34.107
- And the doggie paddle record.

20:34.191 --> 20:35.567
[all laughing]

20:35.651 --> 20:38.153
- Well, uh, I hope it's enough
to push me to my best

20:38.236 --> 20:40.489
and I hope I get on the team.

20:40.572 --> 20:41.406
- Okay.

20:55.796 --> 20:57.631
[powers zapping]

20:57.714 --> 21:04.846
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:04.930 --> 21:06.682
[whistle shrills]

21:06.765 --> 21:16.066
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:16.149 --> 21:19.027
Wow, Jax is
slaughtering Daniel.

21:19.111 --> 21:22.072
- I know. We're totally gonna
win nationals!

21:23.115 --> 21:26.618
- Hey, what are those?
- Oh, these?

21:26.702 --> 21:29.413
They're just my, uh,
new sunglasses.

21:29.496 --> 21:30.706
Custom-made.

21:32.416 --> 21:33.792
Wait!

21:37.212 --> 21:40.674
No way.
He's a witch?

21:43.093 --> 21:46.054
{\an8}<i>[upbeat pop music]</i>

21:46.138 --> 21:54.146
{\an8}<i>♪ ♪</i>
